                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The router is the only component where a Zend_Config object is required, which will be fixed with ZF 2.0.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-30T03:08:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-30T03:08:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34972",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes, any Zend component except router has a method such as setOptions($array) in addition to setConfig(Zend_Config).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-29T11:48:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-29T11:48:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43550",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jkushner1019",
                        "name": "jkushner1019",
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Reid Kushner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is because the bootstrap receives the options array from the application class on instantiation, and when you request options from the bootstrap class, you are receiving a merged version of options in an array format. i think its the standard to have the options in the array format for the application component.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jkushner1019",
                        "name": "jkushner1019",
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Reid Kushner",
